data.name: label7.Text
data.value:
The fonts displayed were auto-installed by FontsInstaller at the first-run of the application.
To see this in action, simply uninstall the fonts displayed then run the application again for the same fonts to be re-installed in your computer. This provides a seamless experience for your users and ensures design consistency in your applications across all Windows devices.
What's even better is that now you won't need to package your applications using an Installer for the required fonts to be installed in any PC! This works great for portable apps and utilities.
Additionally, for non .NET applications and those prefering to use FonsInstaller via the command-line, you can simply use the utility "FontsInstaller.Cmd" for such use cases. It works equally well and is very much simplified for installing individual fonts and entire folders containing fonts. It can also check whether fonts are available in any computer. These and more, will help you get productive with all-things-fonts.
